    <Notice Locale="UK">
        <Text><![CDATA[
※ Please update in an environment where the Bluetooth connection is most stable.
※Update may be unavailable if a Bluetooth Low Energy device (wearable device, smartwatch, etc.) is connected to the Android device (or iOS device). Perform update after disconnecting all Bluetooth devices other than this device from the Android device (or iOS device).
* Please be careful not to update while in riding on vehicles, such as trains, or in environments where 2.4 GHz band radio waves such as Wi-Fi, microwave ovens, cordless phones and many other radio waves are intermingled.

※ Sony | Headphones Connect ※
Please update to the latest version before updating the main unit

[Update details in version 2.0.2]
[1] DSEE HX and Equalizer now function simultaneously.
[2] Improved the event where the volume adjustment bar is unintentionally displayed on some smartphones.
[3] Improved the event where volume operations are not correctly applied even when operated from the smartphone while the music is paused.

*Turn the setting ON on the “Sony|Headphones Connect” app to use both DSEE HX and Equalizer.

[Notes]
1) Software update takes about 30 minutes for Android or about 30 minutes for iOS.
This product continues to function as headphones even when downloading updates and transferring data.
2)Perform update after confirming that the remaining battery charge is sufficient on the headphones and Android device (or iOS device).

[How to check the software version]
Select [WI-1000XM2 Version] from the upper right menu of Sony | Headphones Connect application screen. 


YOU SHOULD CAREFULLY READ THE BELOW BEFORE UPDATING YOUR SOFTWARE.

This product contains software, the title to and copyright in which are owned and controlled by Sony Home Entertainment & Sound Products Inc., affiliates of Sony Home Entertainment & Sound Products Inc. (“Sony Group Company”) and/or its third party licensors. The software is protected by copyright laws, international copyright treaties and any other intellectual property laws. You may only use the software as a part of functions provided by the product, unless otherwise granted by a separate license agreement made between you and Sony Home Entertainment & Sound Products Inc., Sony Group Company and/or its third party licensors.

This update program shall be provided to update the software of this product for the purpose of (i) upgrading security function, (ii) bug fix or error modification, and (iii) upgrading update features. You expressly acknowledge and agree that use of the update program shall not correct all bugs or errors in the software incorporated in the product. By installing this update program, the function of the software may be added, changed or deleted.

The title and copyright of the updated software shall belong to Sony Home Entertainment & Sound Products Inc., Sony Group Company and/or third party licensors.

Sony Home Entertainment & Sound Products Inc., Sony Group Company and third party licensors shall not be liable for any loss or damage arising from the performance or non-performance of such updated program.

The above terms shall not limit your rights granted by any applicable law.



